metadata.name: Neural Collapse #231
metadata.description:
What happens when your brain overloads, or when you lose control of your giant robot.

A study on the repetition and stacking of a simple but very dynamic structure.

Everything procedurally generated at runtime.
You can find more informations on the piece, its design and origins, here: https://ulucode.com/wp/neural-collapse/

Interactivity : 
- You can hover your mouse on the connectors to close them... temporarily
- Press and hold the mouse button to slightly move the viewpoint.

- Press "a" to increase quality of the antialiasing (3 levels), at the cost of performances. Especially useful on the palettes using outlines.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys 1 to 9 (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels. I recommend starting with "4".

GPU recommended. Best performances on Chrome in general.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #378
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash â€” they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Connected City #11
metadata.description:
A cityscape in a far away world that is lost in space where digital life is to be found either: gone, alive or desert. 

Huge antennas capture space communications defining time and life habits of the population.

Variations include 5 palettes, disposition of buildings, sky and the city lights backdrop. 

Three modes with light, dark and the rare gold one.

- hit 's' for saving a 4096 x 2304 .png file for personal use

metadata.name: Liquid Eternal (Painting Machine) #5
metadata.description: "Liquid Eternal" is the second installment in my Painting Machine series, which aims to translate painterly techniques through generative code. The algorithm for this piece produces a composition of brushstrokes, splatters, and gestures that will continue transforming indefinitely. While the FxPreview command creates a snapshot of the piece at a specific moment in time, the work itself defies any notion of a completed image.

metadata.name: Broken Tiles #45
metadata.description:
This is an homage to all the cheap tacky tiles around the world.

Broken Tiles is initiated by first generating a grid. The grid is then superimposed with Voronoi pattern and displaced with the same grid, resulting in broken and cracked effect. All texture and pattern are generated with nodes in cables.gl, no PNG texture image is used.

Press [s] to capture a 1920x1920 screenshot.



XALTED 2022

metadata.name: Thread Cascade #131
metadata.description:
This project will be reserved and free only for 8 hours, for all the holders of "Laser Paintings" and "Beam"!

The amount of reserves for each user will be equal to the amount of all the token held at 10:45 CEST [UTC+2] on the 4th of July 
(example: user holds 3 "Laser Paintings" and 2 "Beam", will be able to mint "Thread Cascade" 5 times)

WARINING: The reserves will expire 8h after the drop! (at 18:45 CEST [UTC+2] on the 4th of July) And a price for the unlocked mintables will be set (unreserved mints will not be free).

---
